SIMPLE: spline
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spline
<hw>Spline</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
rectangular piece fitting grooves like key seats in a hub and a shaft,
so that while the one may slide endwise on the other, both must revolve
together; a feather; also, sometimes, a groove to receive such a
rectangular piece.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A long, flexible piece of wood sometimes used as a
ruler.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Splining</ent>⟦br⟧
